## Existing Endpoints

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| POST | /api/sessions | Create session |
| GET | /api/sessions/[id] | Get full session data (houses, members, routes, preferences) |
| POST | /api/sessions/[id]/upload | CSV upload (houses) |
| POST/PUT | /api/sessions/[id]/members | Create/update member |
| POST | /api/sessions/[id]/optimize | Generate optimized route |
| DELETE | /api/sessions/[id]/routes/[routeId] | Delete a route |
| GET/PUT | /api/sessions/[id]/preferences | Get/set house preferences |

## Rules

- Session ID comes from URL params, member ID comes from request body
- Return `NextResponse.json({ error: '...' })` with appropriate status for errors
- The main GET endpoint (`/api/sessions/[id]`) assembles the full `SessionData` object — update it when adding new data
- Import database functions from `@/lib/db`, not the db instance directly
